President Trump delivered a speech in the East Room to honor military mothers ahead of Mother's Day. He expressed appreciation for the moms serving in the military, the mothers of military heroes, and the moms with spouses serving in the armed forces. The President acknowledged the sacrifices made by military spouses and the challenges they face in finding employment. He also praised the mothers who raised children that joined the United States Armed Forces and emphasized the strength and courage of the military. President Trump assured the audience that his administration is committed to supporting military mothers and thanked them for their love, devotion, and sacrifice.